            <msContents>
              <summary/>
              <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
              <msItem n="1" xml:id="a1" defective="true">
                <locus from="1a" to="161a">Foll. 1a-161a</locus>
                <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/573">John Chrysostom</author>
                <title ref="" type="supplied">The Commentary of John Chrysostom on the Gospel of S. John, <choice><abbr>homm.</abbr><expan>homilies</expan></choice> i.-xliii.</title>
                <incipit xml:lang="syr">ܡܬܥܠܐ ܠܗ ܡܢ ܥܠܡܐ<locus from="1a"/></incipit>
                <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡ ܠܡܟܬܒ ܒܦܢܩܝܬܐ ܗܕܐ ܡܐܡܪ̈ܐ ܕܛܘܒܢܐ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܐܦܝܣܩܘܦܐ ܕܩܘܣܛܢܛܝܢܦܘܠܝܣ ܐܪ̈ܒܥܝܢ ܘܬܠܬܐ ܕܦܘܫܩܐ ܕܝܘܚܢܢ ܐܘܢܓܠܣܛܐ܀<locus from="161a"/></finalRubric>
                <note>Of these, homm. i., ii.,xxix., and xxxv. are imperfect; whilst <choice><abbr>homm.</abbr><expan>homilies</expan></choice> xxx.-xxxiv. are wanting. The incipit corresponds with the Greek <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀλλ' ἀνωτέρω πάντων ἑστάναι τῶν βιωτικῶν κ.τ.λ.</foreign>, <bibl>Opera, t. viii., p. 2, line 29</bibl>; <bibl>Migne, Patrol. Gr., t. lix., col. 25, line 29</bibl>. The first lacuna extends from <bibl>t. viii., p. 12, line 44, to p. 14, line 18</bibl>; and the second, from <bibl>p. 190, line 9, to p. 236, line 5</bibl>.</note>
              </msItem>
            </msContents>
